# Where to set these for PRODUCTION (e.g. mayaafricanhairbraid.com):
# - If the site is on Vercel: Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#   Add STRIPE_SECRET_KEY and STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (value = key only, no quotes). Then Redeploy.
# - If the site uses Flask (Railway, Render, etc.): set in server env or .env on the host
#
# Add each line as separate variable (Key = name, Value = after =). NO quotes around values.
#
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_your_key_here
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_your_key_here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ_your_key_here
SUPABASE_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co
#
# Required for payments: STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
# stripe-config uses STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (optional - config.js has fallback)
# After saving: Redeploy
